subject: p18517718
History: History of stroke and possible pneumonia. Shortness of breath, tachypnea and decreased O2 sats.
Findings: The previously seen pulmonary edema has resolved. There is no edema, pneumonia, pleural effusion, or pneumothorax. Bibasilar atelectasis is unchanged, including atelectasis in the retrocardiac region. Elevation of the right hemidiaphragm is stable. The cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal. A feeding tube is seen in the stomach with the tip out of the field of view.
Impression: Resolution of pulmonary edema. Stable bibasilar atelectasis.
